   Applications Authored
     _________________________________________________________________
   
   VideoStream Interactive Television Authoring Language
   
   A highly targetted interpreted language designed for interactive
   multimedia applications.
   
   Leland Debugging Platform
   
   A complete program developement and source level debugging system
   designed to work with proprietary hardware for the Super Nintendo and
   Sega Genesis game systems.
   
   Lazarus
   
   A graphics design package that facilitates the creation of tiled
   images for game platforms such as the Super Nintendo and Sega Genesis.
   
   Zardoz 65816 C and Assembly Language Development System
   
   A complete C language development system for the 65816 processor used
   in the Super Nintendo, later models of the Apple II and in many
   embedded systems. The system includes compiler, assembler, linker,
   optimizer, libraries and utilities.
   
   ImageFinder
   
   An image indexing tool that locates all images and creates a database
   with a thumbnail for each and accompanying information that can be
   browsed.
   
   Aztec C
   
   A complete C language development system for the 6502, 80X86, and
   680X0 processors. The system includes compiler, assembler, linker,
   optimizer, source level debugger, libraries and utilities. The system
   was the first available for the Apple II and the Macintosh. It was the
   first third party C development system for the Amiga where it received
   several awards for technical merit and user satisfaction.
   
   Rez
   
   A utility which allows applications on the Amiga to remain resident in
   memory for faster execution times. It also allows multiple executions
   to share code and save memory.
   
   Aquarius
   
   A windowed word processor targetted at the legal profession.
   
   Syntrex OS Windowing System
   
   Video and windowing subsystem of multi-tasking proprietary operating
   system.
   
   Tiny-C
   
   An interpreter for a subset of the C language that ran on 6502 based
   systems such as the KIM-1 and Apple II.
